Date: Thu, 1 Jan 2026 02:34:33 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 12/50] Conduit: Fix PHP 8.1 "substr/trim(null)" exceptions in
 differential.createrawdiff

Summary:
Bail out earlier when we have a raw diff which is empty (null) in order to avoid some PHP 8.x issues.

Passing null to substr() and trim() is deprecated since PHP 8.1.

```
ERROR 8192: substr(): Passing null to parameter #1 ($string) of type string is deprecated at [/var/www/html/phorge/arcanist/src/parser/ArcanistDiffParser.php:194]
ERROR 8192: trim(): Passing null to parameter #1 ($string) of type string is deprecated at [/var/www/html/phorge/arcanist/src/parser/ArcanistDiffParser.php:198]
```

Closes T16429

Test Plan:
* PHP 8.1
* Go to http://phorge.localhost/conduit/method/differential.createrawdiff/ and press "Call Method"

